<p>After junior year I realized I am not sure what I want to do after graduation, and spontaneously decided to take a gap year. I spent the next 14 months exploring different career paths I could pursue post graduation. I spent the first few months in Warsaw, interning at as a strategy analyst at White Star Real Estate and later as an associate consultant at Bain &amp; Company. I then moved to London, where I explored the world of credit risk at Mercuria Energy Trading. Finally, I spent my summer in Singapore working at J.P. Morgan’s investment banking division.</p>

<p>The year off taught me that I want to focus on social impact and entrepreneurship. That’s why I co-founded <span class="bold"><a href="https://newspark.us">newspark</a></span> and became an advisor at <span class="bold"><a href="https://off.org.pl/en/">Our Future Foundation</a></span>.</p>

